<subSubSection id="B091710A4CCACA2B388A88278346ABD7" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="388B72770F014ADDDEBA9AC3E37B902F" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C79C6E5D300BDFD0CD12B6040D1E9349" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Due to the presence of a single, short swimming hair on segments four and five of the third and fourth legs and the shape of palp (Fig. 3A), the single 
<pageBreakToken id="69EF8A8DCCEE23FDCFB019C439B8C774" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" start="start">specimen</pageBreakToken>
from the Chinkualiao stream shows general conformity with 
<taxonomicName id="4EE7C55482C1A8F55E53E29BB8A93D04" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hydrodroma rheophila" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rheophila">Hydrodroma rheophila</taxonomicName>
. As 
<bibRefCitation id="5FCA87AD80E264AA3D5F5F05174F3798" author="Pesic, V" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="1 - 100" title="The water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) of the Balkan peninsula, a revised survey with new records and descriptions of five new taxa." volume="2586" year="2010">
<normalizedToken id="068D9D1076159592AFD74776A8628C3B" originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
et al. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
noted the variability of additional populations tentatively assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="1C68708DCC575580AF5D2C11ECEE9041" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hydrodroma rheophila" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rheophila">Hydrodroma rheophila</taxonomicName>
(e.g. from Greece and Oman, see 
<bibRefCitation id="22AAC63D696E99BC3BE726AF9F3B2174" author="Pesic, V" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="1 - 100" title="The water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) of the Balkan peninsula, a revised survey with new records and descriptions of five new taxa." volume="2586" year="2010">
<normalizedToken id="FB89A428463585D64CA591D5F497E4EA" originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="061F3AD360867742510D7E85B4AE59D2" author="Smit, H" journalOrPublisher="Acarologia" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" pagination="151 - 195" title="New species of water mites from Oman, with some zoogeographical notes (Acari: Hydrachnidia)." url="10.1051/acarologia/20101953" volume="50" year="2010">
Smit and 
<normalizedToken id="D64A8CC74FDC2476F710C48FCDC7407A" originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
, respectively) from different regions of the whole distribution area needs to be examined to clarify the taxonomy. This probably will require the use of molecular approach to examine the degree of genetic differentiation among the geographical populations.
</paragraph>
